vent persisted\");\n}\n```\n\n**What the test demands of `applyBenchmarkTask(db, now)`** — it mutates `db` (the in-memory object holding the collection arrays) AND returns a portal view. Required outcomes:\n\n- **Returned portal view (`after`):** `status` === the exact expectedStatus string; `owner` === `expectedOwners.join(\" + \")` (i.e. `\"Finance + Customer Success + Legal + Operations\"`); `nextStep.length > 8`; `history` === `\"Audit visible\"`; `customerMessage.length > 12`; `riskSummary` === `\"6 signals: invoice, dispute, workflow, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required\"`; `tasks` === `\"4 owner tasks\"`.\n- **Persisted state in `db` (via `assertPersistedState`):**\n  - `db.workflow_state` must contain one item with `requestId === request._id` (`\"invoice-invoice-disp\"`), `status` === expectedStatus, and `riskSignals` array whose `.name` values deep-equal the 6 signal names in order.\n  - `db.owner_tasks` must contain exactly 4 items with `requestId === request._id`, `ownerGroup` values deep-equaling `[\"Finance\", \"Customer Success\", \"Legal\", \"Operations\"]` in order, and every task having truthy `title`, truthy `dueAt`, and `status === \"open\"`.\n  - `db.customer_messages` must contain an item with matching `requestId` and a truthy `body`.\n  - `db.audit_events` must contain an item with matching `requestId` and `customerVisible` truthy.\n\nNote: the portal view is produced by `buildPortalView`, so `applyBenchmarkTask` must write the right shapes into `db` such that `buildPortalView(db)` returns the expected values — OR return its own equivalent view. Since `buildPortalView` already derives all the view fields from the persisted collections, the cleanest path is for `applyBenchmarkTask` to persist correctly into `db` and then return `buildPortalView(db)` (which it currently does). Key detail: `buildPortalView` reads `state.title` and `state.nextStep` from `workflow_state`, derives `riskSummary` from `state.riskSignals`, derives `